ics chairman, Newton Gaines pioneered using ultrasound to sterilize milk, holding patents for the method. A 1931 Science News report described his “terrific squeak” of high-pitched sound waves used to kill bacteria."},{"number":2,"category":"folklore","header":"A kilted professor who threw boomerangs","body":"President of the Texas Folklore Society in 1928, Gaines was an authority on working cowboy songs and recorded for the Library of Congress under John Lomax. Each spring he would don a kilt and many-colored cap to throw boomerangs from a campus hilltop, drawing newspaper notice."},{"number":3,"category":"character","header":"He stenciled “stolen from TCU” on everything","body":"To protect his hard-won, often homemade laboratory apparatus during the Depression, Gaines marked every piece “Stolen from TCU.” At his retirement luncheon his colleagues presented him a brand-new pocketknife, stenciled with the same words — to his great delight."}],"career":[{"role":"Professor of Physics; founding department chairman","organization":"Texas Christian University","start_year":1924,"end_year":1958},{"role":"President","organization":"Texas Folklore Society","start_year":1928,"end_year":1929}],"education":[{"institution_name":"University of Texas at Austin","relationship":"alumnus","years":"1912","degree":"B.S. Electrical Engineering"},{"institution_name":"University of Texas at Austin","relationship":"alumnus","years":"1931","degree":"Ph.D."}],"notable":{"is_notable":true,"notable_category":["science","folklore"],"notable_blurb":"TCU “cowboy physicist”; ultrasound milk-pasteurization patents","primary_url":"https://physics.tcu.edu/history-of-the-department/newton-gaines-cowboy-physicist/","primary_url_label":"Texas Christian University"},"videos":[{"video_id":"VID001"}],"cross_connections":[{"type":"parallel_descent","related_id":"HD3148","link_text":"Eunice Newton Foote","display_label":"a Newton who first described the greenhouse effect, then was forgotten"}],"slug":"samue